# Core Project Structure

The Core project is the foundation of the n-tier architecture and contains:

## Entities
The [Entities](mdc:Core/Entities) directory contains domain models organized by feature:
- [Countries](mdc:Core/Entities/Countries)
- [Cities](mdc:Core/Entities/Cities)
- [Cinemas](mdc:Core/Entities/Cinemas)
- [Movies](mdc:Core/Entities/Movies)

## Shared Components
The [Shared](mdc:Core/Shared) directory contains:

### Data Access
- [Data](mdc:Core/Shared/Data): Database contexts and configurations
- [Repositories](mdc:Core/Shared/Repositories): Repository implementations
- [UnitOfWork](mdc:Core/Shared/UnitOfWork): Unit of Work pattern implementation

### Business Logic
- [Services](mdc:Core/Shared/Services): Services that implement business logic
- [DataProcessings](mdc:Core/Shared/DataProcessings): Data processing utilities

### API Infrastructure
- [Models](mdc:Core/Shared/Models): DTOs and other model classes
- [Endpoints](mdc:Core/Shared/Endpoints): Base classes for API endpoints

### Utilities
- [Configuration](mdc:Core/Shared/Configuration): Application configuration
- [Dictionaries](mdc:Core/Shared/Dictionaries): Enumeration and constant values
- [Extensions](mdc:Core/Shared/Extensions): Extension methods
- [Exceptions](mdc:Core/Shared/Exceptions): Custom exception classes